title: Print, "A pageant on a church feast day", ca. 1600
provenance: Giovanni Piancastelli; Mrs. Edward D. Brandegee
creditline: Museum purchase through gift of various donors and from Eleanor G. Hewitt Fund
description: Horizontal rectangle.  The carriage is drawn by two pairs of cattle toward right.  At the left of a crowned woman sit what probably represent wise and pious men of different ages adn stands St. Michael.  In the paper scroll:  "Carro trionfale della Compania di San Rocco descritto a car.  69. no. 19."  Left corner, top:  "2."  Bottom signature is similar to 1938-88-8549.

tombstone.epitaph:
